OL,7,FBeverley Griggs, consultant in health
OL,8,Fprotection at Public Health Wales,
OL,9,Fsaid: "We are continuing to work with
OL,10,Four partners to investigate this
OL,11,Foutbreak and to reduce the risk of
OL,12,Ffurther transmission.
OL,14,F"Cryptosporidium infection often
OL,15,Fclears up without treatment, but it
OL,16,Fcan be more serious for vulnerable
OL,17,Fpeople.
